  "prompt": "If I delete my Tinder account and uninstall the app, does my profile still show to those I've matched with?",
  "response": "If you delete your Tinder account (not just uninstall the app), your profile and all your matches will be permanently removed from the platform. This means:\n\n1. **Your profile will no longer be visible** to anyone, including those you've matched with.\n2. **Your matches will disappear** from the matches list of the other users.\n3. **You will not be able to recover** your account or matches unless you create a new account and start over.\n\nIf you only uninstall the app without deleting your account, your profile will still be active and visible to your matches until the account is deleted or becomes inactive over time due to inactivity. So, to ensure your profile is completely gone, you need to delete your account through the app or website settings.",
